Program: Thinking Allowed
Title: Creative Britain - Sexology
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/b04pss4x
Last Broadcast Date: Mon 1 Dec 2014
Creative Britain: Laurie Taylor explores its rise and fall with the British historian, Robert Hewison, who provides an assessment of the cultural policies of New Labour and the Coalition. Why has culture failed to escape class? Also, a new Sexology exhibition prompts an analysis of the changing field of sex research. Kaye Wellings, Professor of Sexual & Reproductive Health Research at the London School of Hygiene and Tropical Medicine, charts a history involving book burning, scandal and shame. Producer: Jayne Egerton. Show less